Key Match Events: The match was interrupted by rain with England chasing 158 runs, leading to the Duckworth-Lewis (DL) par score. Ireland was declared winners due to the rain.
Ireland produced a disciplined bowling performance to restrict England's big hitters and celebrated another famous win over England.
The match was the second T20 encounter between England and Ireland, with the first having been washed out in 2010.
Pre-Game Insights: England captain Jos Buttler acknowledged Ireland's excellent performance and admitted England's mistake in the match.
The match was seen as a virtual knockout for England against Australia, which would determine their progression in the tournament.
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler expressed frustration over the loss and highlighted Ireland's disciplined performance.
Ireland's captain Andy Balbirnie was named Man of the Match for his top score of 62 off 47 balls.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The weather conditions affected the match, leading to rain delays and the use of the DL method.
Fans celebrated Ireland's win, with some extending their stay to watch the match.
